<b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>."},{"content":"Add strained bread, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>. Remove mixture from mixing bowl and, with slightly wet hands, form 16 meatballs."},{"content":"Assemble kebabs by placing 1 slice of courgette, 1 meatball, 1 piece of pepper and so on onto the skewers until all ingredients are used up. Moisten and wring a sheet of baking paper then line Varoma tray, making sure to keep some holes unobstructed. Arrange kebabs onto Varoma tray. Clean mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place water and stock paste into mixing bowl, place simmering basket into position with the rice, place Varoma into position and cook:  <b>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. At the end of the cooking time, remove Varoma and simmering basket with aid of spatula, strain rice and set aside."},{"content":"Empty mixing bowl and inside it place olive oil and remaining rosemary and sauté <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>. Season rice with rosemary-flavoured oil."},{"content":"Serve kebabs accompanied by the rice."}],"hintsAndTricks":["If preferred, substitute the marjoram with fresh sage leaves.","At step 7, if preferred, add a pinch of chilli powder.","After cooking in the Varoma, the kebabs can be transferred to a hot frying pan with a dash of oil for several minutes or grilled in the oven."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 40m","2 portion"]}